

=Bio=

Karyotis Theodoros (Greece) Sociologist, translator and activist participating in social movements that promote self-management, solidarity economy and defence of the commons. A member of the Initiative of Solidarity to the Vio.Me. Self-managed Factory, (viome.org) and the Initiative 136 for social control of Thessaloniki’s water services (136.gr). He helps organise the annual Direct Democracy Festival, an international event that brings together collectives, activists and academics around the issue of constructing radical alternatives to capitalism from below. 


